  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "On a form, \"designation\" typically refers to the specific title, role, or category that a person or entity is assigned or identified with. This can include job titles, professional roles, or other classifications relevant to the purpose of the form. For example, on a job application, the designation might be \"Software Engineer\" or \"Marketing Manager.\" In other contexts, it could refer to categories like \"student,\" \"volunteer,\" or \"member.\" The exact meaning can vary depending on the form's purpose and the organization issuing it.",
